{x^2+3x+2 \over x^2-x+1}
 \begin{align} \frac{x^2+3x+2}{x^2-x+1} &=1+\cfrac{4x+1}{x^2-x+1}\\[4pt] &=1+\cfrac1{\frac14x-\frac5{16}+\cfrac{\frac{21}{16}}{4x+1}}\\[4pt] &=1+\cfrac1{\frac14x-\frac5{16}+\cfrac1{\frac{64}{21}x+\frac{16}{21}}} \end{align} 
 1+\cfrac1{\frac14x-\frac5{16}}=\frac{4x+11}{4x-5} 
 (4x+11)(x^2-x+1)-(4x-5)(x^2+3x+2)=21 
\frac{x^2+3x+2}{x^2-x+1}=\frac{1}{\frac{(x^2+3x+2)-(4x+1)}{x^2+3x+2}}=\frac{1}{1-\frac{4x+1}{x^2+3x+2}}
\frac{x^2+3x+2}{4x+1}=\frac{x}{4}+\frac{11}{16}+\frac{21}{16}\frac{1}{4x+1}
\huge \frac{1}{1-\frac{1}{x/4+11/16+\frac{1}{40x/21+10/21}}}. 
